    <grammar_table id="L" title="Stage L: hysterodynamic instrumental and dative" short_title="stage L">
        <description>The hysterodynamic dative and instrumental follow the genitive in acquiring a case marker accent, though the instrumental "perhaps not in all stem classes" (p. 203). (It's reasonable to the assume that this happened under the ergative-absolutive system, while the case marker accent of the genitive was dropped in the non-ergative proterodynamic inflection. But p. 197 also attests a relatively late stage for this change, after the vowel lengthening. In any case, the dative ending in full-grade ablauting -ei can only have moved to the o-stems after this.) The suffix-accented variant of the instrumental cannot have disappeared before the o-stems appeared and took its -h₁ ending, which would afterwards have completely changed to -eh₁. (This stage lies somewhere between stages III and V in the p. 207 table.)</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic" short_title="PD">
                <declension_def id="PD_mf" title="proterodynamic/animate" short_title="mf" />
                <declension_def id="PD_n" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="n" />
            </declension_def>
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic" short_title="HD">
                <declension_def id="HD_A" title="hysterodynamic (some stem classes)" short_title="some" />
                <declension_def id="HD_B" title="hysterodynamic (other stem classes)" short_title="others" />
            </declension_def>
        </declension_def>
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="all-but-G" title="all but genitive/ablative">
                <case_def id="N" title="nominative" short_title="nominative" />
                <case_def id="V" title="vocative" short_title="vocative" />
                <case_def id="Ac" title="accusative" short_title="accusative" />
                <case_def id="L+I+Da" title="locative, instrumental, dative">
                    <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                    <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
                    <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
                </case_def>
            </case_def>
